				<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="544"> 
					<tr>
						<td colspan="2"><b>Directions</b></td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="10" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td width="15">1)</td>
						<td>
						Cut the Chinese cabbage in half. Salt down in 9% salt water.
						</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>2)</td>
						<td>
						Cut the radish into 3x4x0.5cm strips. Salt down. Cut the salted cabbage-heart into the same size.
						</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>3)</td>
						<td>
						Cut the pear into strips like radish. Cut the chestnuts into thin slices. Cut the watercress, leaf mustard, and green onions into 4cm-long strips.
						</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>4)</td>
						<td>
						Skin the small octopus, and pound. Cut into 4cm-long strips. Cut the abalone into thin slices. Slice the fish meat of salt-fermented croaker without the bones. 
						</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>5)</td>
						<td>
						Moisten the pyogo and seogi, and cut them into thick shreds. Cut the green onions, garlic and ginger into fine shreds.
						</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>6)</td>
						<td>
						Mix the seafood and seasonings with cabbage and radish. Mix with red pepper powder and season with salt-fermented croaker liquid.
						</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>7)</td>
						<td>
						In a small porcelain ball, place 2~3 cabbage-leaves and put well-mixed Kimchi on it. Garnish with pyogo, fresh chestnuts, shredded red pepper, and pine nuts. Fold cabbage leaves in order and wrap tight. Put the Kimchi in an earthenware pot.
						</td>
					</tr>
					<tr><td colspan="2"><img src="/common/images/trans.gif" width="1" height="7" border="0"></td></tr>
					<tr valign="top">
						<td>8)</td>
						<td>
						Boil the croaker head and bones completely and cool. Season with salt to 5% to make Kimchi liquid. Pour this over Kimchi and let it fermented in a cool place.
						</td>
					</tr>
